  "doc_id": "36391",
  "text": "Local populations of the mycophagous beetle P. substriatus turn over rapidly and the expected persistence time of any given population is short, of the order of 4-5 years . Because colonization of extinct populations occurs regularly, the persistence of the species is achieved at the metapopulation level as a balance between extinctions and recolonizations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
